How do I check which mode I am in (permissive, enforcing, or disabled)?
	
	Use the getenforce command!
	
	Example: not good :|
	
		[logan@logan /]$ getenforce
		Disabled
		
How do I change mode?

	Use the setenfornce command!
	
	Example: again, not good :| 
	
		[logan@logan /]$ setenforce Enforcing
		setenforce: SELinux is disabled
		
What should I do after changing mode?

	Reboot! Some processes may need to be rebooted to start enforcing SELinux.
	
How do I set the default mode?

	Modify this file: /etc/selinux/config
	
	Then, rre-boot!
	

